      "comment": "ISSY'S STAR (4) returned a strong figure first-up when beaten under a length over today's journey at the Beaumont track. Tired in the final stages when extended to 1300m last time. Nicely in with Stanley's claim and back at 1200m is a serious chance. Honest filly YOU'RE THE CHOICE (8) has been on or about the money all prep. Best rating was two back when beaten a length in a BM64 over this distance at Kembla. Key contender with a repeat of that performance. MISSILE MAGNATE (1) closed late to get up for third when resuming over 1000m at Wyong recently. Has won second-up in the past and another try at today's trip looks timely. FLEET FLYER (3) impressed on debut last start when well supported. Capable of taking this next step.",
